This paper discusses database management systems and query processing, which are core topics in computer science. The focus is on hybrid OLTP and OLAP databases, which are typically studied in the database subfield (cs.DB). The paper also discusses memory management and optimization, which are relevant to data structures (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach for organizing and compressing transactional data, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL).
